ss='e-n-accordion-item-title-header'><div class="e-n-accordion-item-title-text"> Can I get a hearing aid without a hearing test?</div></span> <span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-icon'> <span class='e-opened' ><i aria-hidden="true" class="far fa-angle-up"></i></span> <span class='e-closed'><svg aria-hidden="true" class="e-font-icon-svg e-fas-angle-down" viewBox="0 0 320 512" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M143 352.3L7 216.3c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l22.6-22.6c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l96.4 96.4 96.4-96.4c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l22.6 22.6c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-136 136c-9.2 9.4-24.4 9.4-33.8 0z"></path></svg></span> </span></summary><div role="region" aria-labelledby="e-n-accordion-item-1601" class="elementor-element elementor-element-1bd43e9e e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="1bd43e9e" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container" data-settings="{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-b769d2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="b769d2" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default"><div class="elementor-widget-container"><p>Over-the-counter (OTC) hearing aids can be purchased without a hearing test and are designed for adults with mild to moderate hearing loss. However, a professional hearing evaluation at America’s Best Hearing ensures your hearing devices are tailored to your exact needs and helps rule out medical concerns that may require treatment.</p></div></div></div> </details> <details id="e-n-accordion-item-1602" class="e-n-accordion-item" > <summary class="e-n-accordion-item-title" data-accordion-index="3" tabindex="-1" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="e-n-accordion-item-1602" > <span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-header'><div class="e-n-accordion-item-title-text"> How long do hearing aids last?</div></span> <span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-icon'> <span class='e-opened' ><i aria-hidden="true" class="far fa-angle-up"></i></span> <span class='e-closed'><svg aria-hidden="true" class="e-font-icon-svg e-fas-angle-down" viewBox="0 0 320 512" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M143 352.3L7 216.3c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l22.6-22.6c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l96.4 96.4 96.4-96.4c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l22.6 22.6c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-136 136c-9.2 9.4-24.4 9.4-33.8 0z"></path></svg></span> </span></summary><div role="region" aria-labelledby="e-n-accordion-item-1602" class="elementor-element elementor-element-5165b2f6 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="5165b2f6" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container" data-settings="{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-5f20f3fe elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="5f20f3fe" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default"><div class="elementor-widget-container"><p>On average, hearing aids last about 3 to 7 years. Their lifespan depends on the model, how frequently they’re used, and how well they’re maintained. With regular cleanings, proper care, and check-ups, your devices can stay in great working order longer. Many patients also choose to upgrade sooner to take advantage of new features and advancements in technology.</p></div></div></div> </details> <details id="e-n-accordion-item-1603" class="e-n-accordion-item" > <summary class="e-n-accordion-item-title" data-accordion-index="4" tabindex="-1" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="e-n-accordion-item-1603" > <span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-header'><div class="e-n-accordion-item-title-text"> What is the difference between hearing aids and personal sound amplification products (PSAPs)?</div></span> <span class='e-n-accordion-item-title-icon'> <span class='e-opened' ><i aria-hidden="true" class="far fa-angle-up"></i></span> <span class='e-closed'><svg aria-hidden="true" class="e-font-icon-svg e-fas-angle-down" viewBox="0 0 320 512" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M143 352.3L7 216.3c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l22.6-22.6c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l96.4 96.4 96.4-96.4c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l22.6 22.6c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-136 136c-9.2 9.4-24.4 9.4-33.8 0z"></path></svg></span> </span></summary><div role="region" aria-labelledby="e-n-accordion-item-1603" class="elementor-element elementor-element-af966a9 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="af966a9" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container" data-settings="{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-abbb9fc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="abbb9fc" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default"><div class="elementor-widget-container"><p>Hearing aids are FDA-regulated medical devices designed to treat hearing loss and are custom programmed by a professional to fit your unique hearing needs. PSAPs, on the other hand, are over-the-counter amplifiers intended for people without hearing loss. They make sounds louder but do not offer the same level of precision, personalization, or professional support.</p></div></div></div> </details></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-9cf2d78 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="9cf2d78" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container" data-settings="{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}"><div class="e-con-inner"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-6a9c375 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-child" data-id="6a9c375" data-element_type="container" data-e-type="container" data-settings="{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}"><div class="e-con-inner"><div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e122ee2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="e122ee2" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="headin